To Create Cluster
eksctl create cluster --name my-eks-cluster --nodegroup-name my-worker-node --node-type t2.medium --nodes 2 --managed --region us-east-1"

Cluster Upgradation
1. Control Plane Upgrade
2. Managed Node Group Upgrade
3. Add-on Upgrade

"one minor version at a time" like 1.32 → 1.35 ✅
we can not upgrade like 1.34 → 1.38 ❌

check current version
kubectl version
v1.32

STEP-1
aws eks update-cluster-version --name my-eks-cluster --kubernetes-version 1.33
Wait for Upgrade Completion
it will upgrade API SERVER ,SCHEDULER ,CONTROL MANAGER , ETCD

STEP-2
aws eks update-nodegroup-version --cluster-name my-eks-cluster --nodegroup-name my-worker-node
it will upgrade node groups

STEP-3
aws eks update-addon --cluster-name my-eks-cluster --addon-name coredns
aws eks update-addon --cluster-name my-eks-cluster --addon-name kube-proxy
aws eks update-addon --cluster-name my-eks-cluster --addon-name vpc-cni
it will upgrade addon's



Upgrade Flow for Self-Managed Cluster
1. Upgrade EKS control plane
2. Create new worker nodes with updated AMI
3. Join new nodes to cluster
4. Cordon and drain old nodes
    kubectl drain node-1 --ignore-daemonsets
    Defalut-kubectlcordon node-1
    kubectl uncordon node-1
5. Move workloads
6. Delete old nodes
7. Upgrade EKS add-ons
